==English==

===Noun===
'''abutment'''

#State of [[abutting]].
#That on or against which a body [[abut]]s or [[presses]]; as 
## ''(Architecture):'' The solid part of a pier or wall, etc., which receives the thrust or lateral pressure of an arch, vault, or [[strut]]. - [[Gwilt]]
## ''(Mechanics):'' A fixed point or surface from which [[resistance]] or [[reaction]] is obtained, as the cylinder head of a steam engine, the [[fulcrum]] of a lever, etc. 
## In [[breech-loading]] firearms, the [[block]] behind the [[barrel]] which receives the pressure due to [[recoil]].
 
